| 'to marry (perfective)'
| →
| {{IPA|[sɡlɔɡ]}}
| 'to marry (continuative)'
| {{IPA|(s-''ɡ''-lɔ<u>ɡ</u>)}}
| <small><cite>(Broselow and McCarthy 1984, Walther 2000)</cite></small>
|}

A rare type of reduplication is found in [[Semai language|Semai]] (an Austroasiatic language of Malaysia). "Expressive minor reduplication" is formed with an initial reduplicant that copies the first and last segment of the base:

